    "description": "KG Intelligence CO., LTD. operates as a content provider company. The company offers Wagasha de DOMO! x Alpa Connect, a tool that manage and operate all postings on eAlpa and other aggregate sites all at once; ARPA LINK, a spot work matching app to pinpoint job openings based on time, location, and skills; e-Arra, a recruitment site that provides information on part-time, full-time, and temporary employment; ALPA, a free job information magazine; and ARPA presents the Suitable Job Fair, an introduction site for the suitable job fair. It also provides career counseling, employment support, and job change support services, as well as foreign care human resource development program; Home Building School, a free consultation support service for home building; Rental Style, a website that provides information on rental apartments, condominiums, and detached houses; Rental Style Column; Mom Rental, a website to search for rental properties near elementary and junior high school districts; Kodate Rental, a website that collects and publishes detached houses and rental homes; Kodate Rental Column; Hospita Renta, a website to search for rental properties near hospitals and medical institutions; Hospita Rental Column; Gakuheya Rental; Gakuhair Rental Column; Chukodate!, a website to search for information on purchasing vacant houses, used homes, detached houses, and single-family; Chukoma!; Kaitochi!; IETO; Mom's House Building; Sumai Satei, a real estate sales website for women; and Rental Style Moving Estimates. In addition, the company offers information magazines; Mama Sore, a website that provides news and columns for mothers raising children; human resource development support, competitor store research, human resource recruitment support, and website creation support services; and printing and binding services, including posters, flyers, pamphlets, and free papers. KG Intelligence CO., LTD. was incorporated in 1950 and is headquartered in Okayama, Japan."
